ENTRY       EC 3.1.2.28                 Enzyme
NAME        1,4-dihydroxy-2-naphthoyl-CoA hydrolase;
            menI (gene name);
            ydiL (gene name)
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on ester bonds;
            Thioester hydrolases
SYSNAME     1,4-dihydroxy-2-naphthoyl-CoA hydrolase
REACTION    1,4-dihydroxy-2-naphthoyl-CoA + H2O = 1,4-dihydroxy-2-naphthoate + CoA [RN:R07262]
ALL_REAC    R07262
SUBSTRATE   1,4-dihydroxy-2-naphthoyl-CoA [CPD:C15547];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     1,4-dihydroxy-2-naphthoate [CPD:C03657];
            CoA [CPD:C00010]
COMMENT     This enzyme participates in the synthesis of menaquinones [4], phyloquinone [3], as well as several plant pigments [1,2]. The enzyme from the cyanobacterium Synechocystis sp. PCC 6803 does not accept benzoyl-CoA or phenylacetyl-CoA as substrates [3].
